1
00:01:26,550 --> 00:01:34,970
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,420 --> 00:01:37,950
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:40,130
You care that much?

4
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,190
Of course I care.

5
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:44,270
I don't want you to misunderstand.

6
00:01:46,650 --> 00:01:49,009
Laugh if you want to.

7
00:01:49,070 --> 00:01:50,020
I don't want to.

8
00:01:56,710 --> 00:01:57,570
Then cry.

9
00:01:58,490 --> 00:01:59,430
Sit properly.

10
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:11,740
The thing is,
that dish was really delicious.

11
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:15,160
Not as delicious
as the food that girl brought.

12
00:02:16,790 --> 00:02:17,800
That girl and I—

13
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:19,310
we really don't know each other.

14
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:21,450
She just suddenly brought food over.

15
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:22,460
Really.

16
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:24,340
I didn't eat a single bite of her food.

17
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,740
I told her to take it away.

18
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,579
Who knows?

19
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:28,400
What do you mean by that?

20
00:02:28,810 --> 00:02:30,530
Next time

21
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,040
you bring me food,

22
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:33,090
if you see that girl,

23
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:34,030
I'll have her tell you.

24
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:34,800
I'm not going.

25
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,400
Let that girl bring it to you.

26
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,370
Alright.

27
00:02:39,970 --> 00:02:40,829
Alright?

28
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:00,410
Last time you came alone

29
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:01,520
and asked me to arrange it for you.

30
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,470
I did it for Director Weng's sake,

31
00:03:02,470 --> 00:03:03,280
didn't I?

32
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,000
Now you brought all these outsiders here.

33
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,190
Aren't you just being unreasonable?

34
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,630
Our projection room
isn't open to the public.

35
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,500
Not to mention
there are leaders here today.

36
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,960
I can't help you with this.

37
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,340
I just can't.

38
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:13,840
Shengli. Shengli.

39
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,280
We are not watching the movie.

40
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,130
Call him out so we can beat him up.

41
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,090
Let's just forget it.

42
00:03:16,090 --> 00:03:17,370
We shouldn't cause you any trouble.

43
00:03:17,370 --> 00:03:17,900
Exactly.

44
00:03:18,579 --> 00:03:19,910
Anyway,

45
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:21,890
we still got to hang out together.

46
00:03:22,579 --> 00:03:23,620
Right, don't worry.

47
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,810
If it doesn't work out,
you guys can watch.

48
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:26,120
I'll take her on your new bike

49
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:26,810
for a spin.

50
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:27,960
A spin?

51
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,900
You don't know the way. If you get lost,

52
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:29,680
we'll have to go looking for you.

53
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,060
Wait!

54
00:03:30,410 --> 00:03:30,860
Wait!

55
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,560
What's up?

56
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,079
I have an idea.

57
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:38,020
Will it work?

58
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:39,030
It will.

59
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,060
Let's go up.

60
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,500
We just want to watch a movie.

61
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,030
Why are we sneaking around?

62
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:45,680
Shut up.

63
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:46,530
Will you die if you don't talk?

64
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,210
I'll take you to buy the tickets. Come on.

65
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:49,620
Hurry up. Come up here.

66
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,960
Not even dating is this hard.

67
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,230
What's going on?

68
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,180
Hurry up.

69
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,780
Don't make me late for the movie.

70
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:00,560
How can a grown man

71
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,810
-be afraid of heights?
-Are you scared or not?

72
00:04:01,810 --> 00:04:03,210
Don't talk so much
if your legs are shaking.

73
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:04,300
I'm not scared.

74
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:06,360
-Hurry up.
-Look how scared you are.

75
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:10,110
Director.

76
00:04:10,810 --> 00:04:12,400
I think our script

77
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,600
is better than this.

78
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,430
If you were the director,

79
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,190
it would definitely be better.

80
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,519
This is a classic.

81
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:28,650
[No Smoking]

82
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,430
We can actually watch it from here?

83
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,640
[The end]

84
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:38,870
[The End]

85
00:05:40,390 --> 00:05:42,190
Why are there people in the back?

86
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:43,909
Who are you?

87
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:44,940
Come out!

88
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:46,100
Staff!

89
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:47,040
Go backstage quickly!

90
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:47,720
Bye-bye!

91
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,100
See ya!

92
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,310
We should thank Mr. Xu

93
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:53,500
for letting us

94
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,570
watch the movie today.

95
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,480
Thank you, Mr. Xu!

96
00:05:57,570 --> 00:05:58,690
-You're welcome.
-Thank you, Mr. Xu.

97
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:00,610
Your sister always helps you

98
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:01,690
dress up so nicely.

99
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:03,060
Aren't you going to thank her?

100
00:06:03,060 --> 00:06:04,630
I'll thank her personally.

101
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:05,640
Personally?

102
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,510
Then should your sister also

103
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,110
thank Mr. Xu personally?

104
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,430
Who's pedaling?

105
00:06:11,450 --> 00:06:13,180
Who's holding the handlebars?

106
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:15,120
Why don't you sing a song?

107
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,140
Okay.

108
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:16,860
Okay.

109
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:23,140
Should auld acquaintance be forgot

110
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:27,660
and never brought to mind?

111
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:32,860
Should auld acquaintance be forgot.

112
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:35,370
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

113
00:06:32,930 --> 00:06:37,250
And auld lang syne?

114
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:41,260
♪ And never brought to mind? ♪

115
00:06:42,050 --> 00:06:47,670
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

116
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:53,650
♪ And auld lang syne? ♪

117
00:06:54,830 --> 00:07:00,450
♪ We twa hae run about the braes ♪

118
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:06,610
♪ And pou'd the gowans fine ♪

119
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:12,770
♪ But we've wander'd monie a weary fit ♪

120
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:19,490
♪ Sin' auld lang syne ♪

121
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:22,330
Master.

122
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:23,570
While you were away,

123
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,860
I kept the house

124
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:25,810
clean,

125
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:27,010
tidy, and spotless.

126
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,720
Much better than when you were here.

127
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:30,390
Great.

128
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:30,850
Come on.

129
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:32,830
Wait a minute.

130
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:35,030
You live here alone,

131
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:36,750
with no one to supervise

132
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,159
or criticize you.

133
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:40,270
You must be living freely.

134
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:42,000
Not at all.

135
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:43,659
While you were away,

136
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:45,220
I felt like the house was

137
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,800
missing a kind of celestial aura.

138
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,730
Celestial aura?

139
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,680
You mean a demonic aura, don't you?

140
00:07:50,690 --> 00:07:53,370
A thousand-year-old demon then.

141
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,000
Cut the chatter.

142
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,180
A surprise inspection.

143
00:07:57,180 --> 00:07:59,230
Read our script.

144
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:00,620
Let me see

145
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:02,520
if you have made any progress.

146
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:03,390
Hurry up.

147
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:03,890
Okay.

148
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,130
Then let me help you sit down.

149
00:08:05,130 --> 00:08:05,330
Come here.

150
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:05,750
Okay.

151
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:06,470
Okay.

152
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:06,980
Okay.

153
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:09,600
Okay.

154
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,600
Be careful.

155
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,060
Okay, sit down.

156
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:14,300
Okay.

157
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,680
Hurry up.

158
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:16,300
Hurry up.

159
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:17,930
Read the script.

160
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:18,800
Hurry up.

161
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:26,050
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng]

162
00:08:26,870 --> 00:08:27,470
Hurry up.

163
00:08:28,890 --> 00:08:29,480
Hurry up.

164
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:30,980
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng]

165
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,890
[The Late Love, Script by Xu]

166
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,350
From now on, in the troupe,

167
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:52,870
[Fenghua Song and Dance Troupe]

168
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,340
you should learn from the other teachers.

169
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:48,890
Okay.

170
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,500
Call me if you need anything.

171
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:50,890
Okay.

172
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,080
After you go back,

173
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,280
say hello to your dad.

174
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,300
My dad says hello to you too.

175
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,420
You're too polite.

176
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,920
It's a small thing.

177
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:58,730
Go now.

178
00:08:58,770 --> 00:08:59,370
Director.

179
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,000
My dad said

180
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:02,600
our troupe's performance
at his company last time was

181
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,490
very successful.

182
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:05,170
This is for you.

183
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:06,400
You are too polite.

184
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:08,470
Be sure to pass on my greetings.

185
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:09,360
Thank you, Director.

186
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,620
-Get in the car.
-Okay.

187
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:14,840
Bye, Director.

188
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,630
Master.

189
00:09:39,770 --> 00:09:41,740
While I was recovering

190
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,360
in Sichuan,

191
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,500
I never expected

192
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:50,020
you to change the script

193
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,050
like this.

194
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,590
Didn't you tell me

195
00:09:56,010 --> 00:09:56,970
to be bold

196
00:09:57,290 --> 00:09:58,600
and go all out?

197
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:01,000
You

198
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,320
really went all out.

199
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,250
You gave it your all.

200
00:10:07,010 --> 00:10:08,750
You weren't just copying.

201
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:11,290
This draft

202
00:10:12,890 --> 00:10:14,860
is half mine

203
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:17,720
and half yours.

204
00:10:18,630 --> 00:10:19,410
M-Master.

205
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,850
I... I just wrote it...

206
00:10:21,940 --> 00:10:22,580
for fun.

207
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:23,860
I read it to you...

208
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,360
just to make you laugh.

209
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,240
I copied the script you told me to copy.

210
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,410
I'll read it to you now.

211
00:10:28,410 --> 00:10:29,550
No need.

212
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:31,310
That draft

213
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:32,690
has been scrapped.

214
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:34,470
Come on.

215
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:38,410
Bring the script here.

216
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:40,610
Get a pen.

217
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:42,540
Well...

218
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:43,440
Hurry.

219
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:45,040
Bring it here.

220
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:46,300
The version

221
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:47,480
you just read.

222
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:48,850
Bring it here.

223
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,900
Just bring it over!

224
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:04,290
The pen.

225
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:14,700
[The Late Love]

226
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:22,500
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter]

227
00:11:29,050 --> 00:11:34,090
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Sheng]

228
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:35,910
Master!

229
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,010
You can't do this!

230
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:36,960
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

231
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:37,540
Master,

232
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:38,510
being able to learn from you

233
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:39,370
is already enough for me!

234
00:11:39,370 --> 00:11:40,940
You... you really can't do this!

235
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:42,030
Bring the liquor.

236
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,780
Get the liquor. Hurry.

237
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:44,680
Hurry up!

238
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,650
Get the liquor!

239
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:49,900
Come on.

240
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:52,850
Fill the cups.

241
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:54,630
Fill the cups.

242
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:00,580
Come on.

243
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,770
Cheers.

244
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:16,050
This is a script

245
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:15,510
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

246
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,070
co-written by me

247
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:20,580
and Xu Shengli.

248
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:22,480
It's done.

249
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:25,130
It's perfect!

250
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:28,770
Master.

251
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:29,930
Master...

252
00:12:29,930 --> 00:12:31,530
Master, you'll always be my teacher!

253
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:32,820
No, you'll always be my master!

254
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:34,220
I'll always love you!

255
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,320
W-Wait a minute.

256
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:36,590
Listen to me.

257
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:39,200
I'm not your master.

258
00:12:39,870 --> 00:12:41,080
I'm your teacher,

259
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,450
one of your many teachers.

260
00:12:45,170 --> 00:12:47,150
You have a boundless future.

261
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:48,690
In this life,

262
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:51,290
being your teacher

263
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:54,000
makes me incredibly proud.

264
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,300
You are my master!

265
00:13:02,130 --> 00:13:03,890
Be careful! Be careful!

266
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,250
Be careful! Be careful!

267
00:13:07,130 --> 00:13:10,620
[Guest Room]

268
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:16,570
[Guest Room]

269
00:13:13,770 --> 00:13:14,290
Sir.

270
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,150
Going out?

271
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:16,750
What's wrong with your leg?

272
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:17,870
Nothing.

273
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,670
I just wore a hole in this shoe
from working.

274
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:22,870
Your back is bad, so don't work too much.

275
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:25,810
That's heartwarming.

276
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:27,260
I've got to go.

277
00:13:27,630 --> 00:13:28,030
Okay.

278
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:33,980
[Guest Room]

279
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,450
Come back early.

280
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:57,860
Excuse me.

281
00:13:57,860 --> 00:13:58,890
Are you

282
00:13:58,890 --> 00:14:00,230
doing some performance art here?

283
00:14:00,230 --> 00:14:00,980
Art?

284
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,970
I think you are quite artistic.

285
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,700
I-I do art.

286
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:08,830
[Welcome Qigong Master Cao Guangtai
for Teaching and Demonstration]

287
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,340
Welcome...

288
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:11,830
Cao Guangtai?

289
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:14,940
Let yourself and nature

290
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,650
resonate with each other

291
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,530
in every breath.

292
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:22,640
[No smoking]

293
00:14:20,370 --> 00:14:22,010
Exhale...

294
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:25,050
Inhale...

295
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:28,530
Uncle.

296
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:31,020
I...

297
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:41,890
Nephew.

298
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:43,900
Have a seat.

299
00:14:47,170 --> 00:14:47,770
Thank you.

300
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:03,180
Isn't it ice cold

301
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,940
and refreshing?

302
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:06,720
It's been chilled.

303
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:07,900
Of course it's cold.

304
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:09,620
Ice cold

305
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,500
refers to external cold,

306
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,960
while the cold in qi refers to
internal cold.

307
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:16,230
External cold dissipates in an instant,

308
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:19,100
while internal cold lingers.

309
00:15:19,170 --> 00:15:20,240
Uncle, why do you talk

310
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,740
in such a rehearsed way now?

311
00:15:21,740 --> 00:15:22,860
And I can't hear

312
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,240
any Shanxi accent at all.

313
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,890
It has a bit of a Beijing accent

314
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:27,690
and a hint of a Northeast accent.

315
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,390
I'm somewhat of a wanderer,

316
00:15:32,530 --> 00:15:33,660
traveling all over.

317
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:35,550
Especially here,

318
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:38,010
if I didn't speak
with a little Beijing accent,

319
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:39,600
how could I

320
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,480
strut around?

321
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:43,290
With that thick hometown accent of yours,

322
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:44,770
you'd better change it soon.

323
00:15:44,770 --> 00:15:45,970
It'll be good for you.

324
00:15:48,220 --> 00:15:49,460
I never expected

325
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,410
that we would run into each other.

326
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:55,260
Aren't you a master now?

327
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:57,990
Didn't you predict
that I would be in Beijing?

328
00:15:59,410 --> 00:16:00,360
Alright, alright.

329
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,290
Alright, Uncle.

330
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:03,050
I know

331
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:05,370
you used to smash boulders on your chest
at the village entrance,

332
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:06,220
and your body

333
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,150
just couldn't take it anymore, right?

334
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,010
I heard from my dad

335
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:08,550
that you went to the Northeast

336
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:09,550
to read fortunes.

337
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,130
How come you ran over here
in the blink of an eye

338
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:12,660
and became a qigong master?

339
00:16:16,170 --> 00:16:16,550
Uncle,

340
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,790
you've been coughing for a while.

341
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:19,920
Drink some water to catch your breath.

342
00:16:20,890 --> 00:16:22,510
You made me this mad.

343
00:16:33,650 --> 00:16:34,740
You came to Beijing

344
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:36,370
to paint?

345
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:37,390
What else?

346
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,670
There's nothing else I can do.

347
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:39,530
Looks like you

348
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:41,930
haven't made a name for yourself painting.

349
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,770
Tell me,

350
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,840
how are you doing?

351
00:16:46,740 --> 00:16:48,910
Let's see if I can help you.

352
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:50,390
We don't

353
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,390
see each other much,

354
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:55,530
but we are Caos.

355
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,650
We have the Cao family blood.

356
00:16:58,390 --> 00:17:00,130
As long as you're willing to join me,

357
00:17:00,130 --> 00:17:02,080
I welcome you with open arms.

358
00:17:03,010 --> 00:17:04,329
Give it a rest, Uncle.

359
00:17:04,510 --> 00:17:05,589
I am a painter,

360
00:17:05,589 --> 00:17:06,460
an artist.

361
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:07,599
You are a con...

362
00:17:11,220 --> 00:17:12,150
A Qigong master.

363
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,780
We are not in the same field.

364
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,160
You are being narrow-minded.

365
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:19,750
Qigong is also an art.

366
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:20,880
It does look like

367
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:21,900
performance art.

368
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,700
Go back and think about it.

369
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:25,640
If you come, it is fate.

370
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:27,030
If not, it is not.

371
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,080
Okay, thanks anyway, Uncle.

372
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:30,880
And remember,

373
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:34,440
when you encounter things
you don't understand,

374
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,970
don't jump to conclusions.

375
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:39,050
You might get struck by lightning.

376
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:43,030
Right, Uncle.

377
00:17:43,590 --> 00:17:44,250
About this,

378
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,810
you should remind those who

379
00:17:45,810 --> 00:17:47,050
were carrying the pot on their heads.

380
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:48,500
If it rains

381
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,220
or there's lightning,

382
00:17:49,220 --> 00:17:50,250
don't carry it and run

383
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:50,880
outside.

384
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,050
It's a real conductor.

385
00:17:52,050 --> 00:17:53,090
If it attracts lightning

386
00:17:53,090 --> 00:17:53,830
and you get struck,

387
00:17:53,830 --> 00:17:55,560
it would be quite troublesome.

388
00:17:59,050 --> 00:17:59,710
Checkmate.

389
00:18:02,330 --> 00:18:02,790
Sir.

390
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:05,970
Looking for Liangliang? He's not here.

391
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:06,980
Take this.

392
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:09,010
What is it?

393
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:11,120
Take a look and you'll know.

394
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:13,610
Alright. Let me see.

395
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:20,030
Is it for Liangliang?

396
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:21,170
It's for you.

397
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:21,960
Your shoes

398
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:22,980
are so worn out.

399
00:18:22,980 --> 00:18:23,910
Throw them away.

400
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:25,810
They're for me?

401
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:28,020
What? They...

402
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:28,740
are for me?

403
00:18:29,270 --> 00:18:30,670
I don't want them.

404
00:18:31,660 --> 00:18:32,460
Take it.

405
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:33,250
You're my uncle.

406
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:34,980
What's wrong with me
buying you a pair of shoes?

407
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:35,440
Well...

408
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:36,860
How...

409
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:38,090
how much?

410
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:42,050
Not expensive.
I bought them on the way back.

411
00:18:42,610 --> 00:18:43,410
What's wrong?

412
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:45,130
Are you not my uncle anymore?

413
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:47,600
Why are you talking like that?

414
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:48,810
Ranran,

415
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,630
next time

416
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:51,550
if you want to buy something
on the way again,

417
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:52,310
think of...

418
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:53,680
Okay.

419
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:55,210
What do you want?

420
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:57,510
I like jeans.

421
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,200
How could you take advantage like that?

422
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:00,580
Okay.

423
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:01,980
I'll buy you a pair when I get my pay.

424
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:02,400
No, no.

425
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:03,400
I was kidding.

426
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:05,160
I was kidding with her.

427
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:05,770
Come on.

428
00:19:05,810 --> 00:19:06,400
I'm not like you,

429
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:07,440
holding a new pair of shoes

430
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,380
and completely forgetting
the real business.

431
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:09,780
Right.

432
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,430
I was just about to find you.

433
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:13,170
Ranran, do you know

434
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:15,030
what's going on with Liangliang
these days?

435
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:16,360
Did you two have a fight?

436
00:19:18,980 --> 00:19:20,200
We didn't.

437
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:21,980
Then why is it that every day
when he comes back,

438
00:19:21,980 --> 00:19:23,030
he slams things around

439
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:24,640
or just goes straight to the bed

440
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,700
without saying a word?

441
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:27,110
It's been 3 days.

442
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:31,850
He

443
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:35,500
has been in a bad mood recently.

444
00:19:36,770 --> 00:19:38,550
But as for what exactly it is,

445
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:41,480
he might be more willing to tell you.

446
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:47,830
I have to go back

447
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:48,640
to memorize lines

448
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:49,550
and read the script.

449
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:50,900
If these shoes pinch,

450
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:51,530
tell me immediately

451
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:52,940
so I can exchange them for you.

452
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:53,740
Thank you.

453
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,300
Come to me if you need anything.

454
00:19:58,310 --> 00:19:59,250
Rest early.

455
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:01,610
This kid.

456
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:02,830
She's so nice.

457
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:04,070
Such a good girl.

458
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:06,570
Didn't you say kid?

459
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:07,480
That works too.

460
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:14,240
Get up.

461
00:20:15,570 --> 00:20:16,770
We are playing chess.

462
00:20:17,810 --> 00:20:19,280
You're quite something.

463
00:20:19,590 --> 00:20:20,810
You haven't said a word for 3 days,

464
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:23,010
and when you did, you just said "get up."

465
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,130
Liangliang.

466
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:36,980
Look.

467
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:39,110
These are the new shoes

468
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:40,450
Ranran gave me.

469
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,880
They are so good.

470
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:47,380
Cao,

471
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:50,120
what did Ranran say she'd give you?

472
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:50,870
Jeans.

473
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,010
And she said she'd get me

474
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:53,010
a pair of brand name ones.

475
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:54,800
Lee or something.

476
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,120
Lee Cooper.

477
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:57,450
Yes, that's the name.

478
00:20:57,850 --> 00:20:59,680
That's a famous brand.

479
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,140
Right?

480
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:01,350
This girl Ranran,

481
00:21:01,350 --> 00:21:02,420
she really is nice.

482
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,370
She really is.

483
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,510
She just takes pity on me.

484
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:06,010
You?

485
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:07,880
I'd say she takes pity on me.

486
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:10,080
What do you two have to be pitiful about?

487
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,930
Who are you trying to annoy?

488
00:21:12,050 --> 00:21:13,460
What are you putting on a show for?

489
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:14,900
Who's annoying who?

490
00:21:15,510 --> 00:21:16,250
And you weren't putting on a show?

491
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:17,460
You've been acting all pitiful for days.

492
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:19,090
Are you in a drama or something?

493
00:21:19,090 --> 00:21:20,350
You've been like this

494
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,030
for 3 days.

495
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:22,110
Who are you acting for?

496
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:22,590
What?

497
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,460
The young master
from Beijing is acting like

498
00:21:23,460 --> 00:21:24,380
it's hard when it's really not, isn't he?

499
00:21:24,380 --> 00:21:26,220
What's wrong with being from Beijing?

500
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:28,080
What advantage does that give us?

501
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:33,330
I thought

502
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:37,260
I didn't get into
that song and dance troupe last time

503
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:39,010
because I wasn't good enough.

504
00:21:39,290 --> 00:21:40,380
I was thinking of saving money

505
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:42,400
to get a teacher to improve my skills.

506
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,380
But I didn't expect it
to be an inside job.

507
00:21:44,380 --> 00:21:46,500
It has nothing to do with ability at all.

508
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,290
I just like playing the saxophone.

509
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:49,260
I asked around

510
00:21:49,290 --> 00:21:50,790
how to get into this circle.

511
00:21:50,790 --> 00:21:51,570
They told me

512
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,440
you need connections.

513
00:21:54,550 --> 00:21:56,080
Once you have connections,

514
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,540
you can find a stepping stone.

515
00:21:59,380 --> 00:22:02,040
How much do you think
this stepping stone costs?

516
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:05,060
I play in underpasses.

517
00:22:05,090 --> 00:22:06,190
I play in bars.

518
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:07,880
When will I ever be able to afford

519
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:08,610
this stone?

520
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,830
What's wrong with being from Beijing?

521
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:14,770
You guys are always going on

522
00:22:14,770 --> 00:22:16,370
about me being from Beijing.

523
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:25,980
I know.

524
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:28,980
You can't go home.

525
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:32,050
But this is your home too.

526
00:22:34,420 --> 00:22:35,150
Don't you...

527
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,180
have us?

528
00:22:38,250 --> 00:22:39,350
Why are you crying?

529
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:45,010
Well, you know...

530
00:22:46,050 --> 00:22:47,240
I would have spent it

531
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:50,610
if it weren't for being 10 yuan short.

532
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,760
That's all my savings.

533
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:02,690
You have to buy me a meal every day.

534
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,330
Take it. Take it.

535
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:08,770
Here.

536
00:23:16,740 --> 00:23:18,070
What if I take this money

537
00:23:23,090 --> 00:23:24,420
and it doesn't work out?

538
00:23:28,850 --> 00:23:30,110
Just consider it lost.

539
00:23:31,090 --> 00:23:31,550
Anyway,

540
00:23:32,650 --> 00:23:34,050
we've lost money before.

541
00:23:34,290 --> 00:23:36,030
Just consider it blown away by the wind.

542
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:37,030
Yeah, blown away.

543
00:23:45,010 --> 00:23:46,790
D-Don't feel bad anymore.

544
00:23:49,810 --> 00:23:52,010
I'll come back to try on the shoes later.

545
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:06,570
Director,

546
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,430
what's the studio's opinion now?

547
00:24:09,110 --> 00:24:09,960
Are there some parts in the script

548
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:10,570
that

549
00:24:10,610 --> 00:24:12,010
they didn't understand?

550
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:14,400
Director,

551
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,250
just tell me.

552
00:24:16,310 --> 00:24:17,030
Your sighing

553
00:24:17,030 --> 00:24:18,240
makes my heart sink.

554
00:24:20,090 --> 00:24:20,660
Xu.

555
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:24,300
I'm not trying to discourage you.

556
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:26,090
But there are some situations

557
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:28,020
that I must explain to you clearly.

558
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:30,980
These opinions from the studio

559
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:32,950
are just a formality.

560
00:24:33,830 --> 00:24:34,500
Which means

561
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:36,310
the studio is not going to film it.

562
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:37,450
Wh-Why is that?

563
00:24:37,850 --> 00:24:38,830
Kid, kid.

564
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:41,810
Some things

565
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:44,160
are about the people,

566
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:45,640
not the script.

567
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:47,370
What about this movie?

568
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,090
It's such a great story,

569
00:24:51,090 --> 00:24:52,250
and it was personally produced

570
00:24:52,250 --> 00:24:53,410
by you and Mr. He.

571
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:54,790
So that's it?

572
00:24:55,350 --> 00:24:56,410
It can't be filmed?

573
00:24:58,530 --> 00:24:59,860
Let's not talk about me.

574
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,400
Mr. He spent so many years

575
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,530
writing this story.

576
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,420
Now that his eyes are like this,

577
00:25:05,420 --> 00:25:06,160
when will he be able to write

578
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:07,130
his next story?

579
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:08,350
Or will he even

580
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,400
have a next story?

581
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,260
They say...

582
00:25:12,790 --> 00:25:14,250
scripts are our children.

583
00:25:14,610 --> 00:25:14,990
Well,

584
00:25:15,510 --> 00:25:16,250
every child

585
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:17,470
has a different fate.

586
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:21,200
Sometimes,

587
00:25:21,610 --> 00:25:23,610
the encounters and partings in life

588
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:26,610
just require patient waiting.

589
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:31,920
I won't change it!

590
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:33,910
Not a single word.

591
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,420
It's an art film,

592
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:37,900
and they have to turn it
into a commercial one.

593
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:39,050
It's so weird.

594
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:41,250
It's ridiculous!

595
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:42,710
Ridiculous!

596
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:55,040
From the day I became a screenwriter

597
00:25:55,610 --> 00:25:57,470
and wrote my first word until now,

598
00:25:58,140 --> 00:25:59,200
it's been 36 years.

599
00:26:01,010 --> 00:26:01,610
I know

600
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:04,030
that for every word I write,

601
00:26:04,810 --> 00:26:07,610
there's always someone
who might have an opinion.

602
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:10,850
But the scripts I write

603
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:13,090
are like my own children.

604
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:14,900
If someone

605
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,220
broke their legs

606
00:26:16,850 --> 00:26:18,310
and gouged out their eyes,

607
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:20,480
would that be okay?

608
00:26:20,530 --> 00:26:21,000
No.

609
00:26:24,220 --> 00:26:25,090
Some scripts

610
00:26:26,530 --> 00:26:28,980
are like the girl in my heart

611
00:26:29,420 --> 00:26:31,220
with beautiful single eyelids.

612
00:26:33,350 --> 00:26:35,590
If you ask her to change her makeup

613
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,740
and make her cheeks bright red,

614
00:26:39,610 --> 00:26:40,340
is that okay?

615
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:41,680
Yes.

616
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,810
But if they take her away

617
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:51,140
and give her double eyelid surgery,

618
00:26:51,790 --> 00:26:52,920
can you tolerate it?

619
00:26:53,330 --> 00:26:54,010
No!

620
00:26:55,110 --> 00:26:55,690
Exactly.

621
00:26:56,290 --> 00:26:56,660
Master,

622
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:58,050
but this is your hard work.

623
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,590
It's your hard work too!

624
00:27:10,350 --> 00:27:13,460
There's 10,000 yuan on the desk.

625
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:15,570
Take it.

626
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:18,090
I'm used

627
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,620
to being alone.

628
00:27:21,850 --> 00:27:23,310
I don't need to save money.

629
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,090
Just consider it

630
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:27,080
as your manuscript fee.

631
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,330
I can't take this money.

632
00:27:29,550 --> 00:27:31,250
You need money for your medical treatment.

633
00:27:31,250 --> 00:27:32,050
Stop nagging!

634
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,340
From now on,

635
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,360
we

636
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:41,400
will go our separate ways.

637
00:27:42,940 --> 00:27:45,920
I have a few words to say to you.

638
00:27:48,310 --> 00:27:50,880
Don't complain to others.

639
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:55,460
Don't tell others
that you're having a hard time.

640
00:27:56,590 --> 00:27:59,010
Don't glorify a tragedy.

641
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,220
Do you remember the movie

642
00:28:03,030 --> 00:28:05,250
"Lenin in 1918"?

643
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:09,140
Moscow was running out of food.

644
00:28:10,070 --> 00:28:12,090
Lenin asked Vasily to bring some.

645
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:16,420
Vasily narrowly escaped death

646
00:28:17,090 --> 00:28:18,950
and delivered the food to Moscow.

647
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:20,830
Lenin said,

648
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,000
"Comrade Vasily,

649
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:24,750
I heard

650
00:28:25,290 --> 00:28:26,420
you were surrounded

651
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,480
and went through many battles."

652
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:32,330
Vasily replied...

653
00:28:34,740 --> 00:28:35,670
Vasily replied,

654
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:40,360
"That was inevitable!"

655
00:28:40,740 --> 00:28:41,290
Right.

656
00:28:43,820 --> 00:28:44,940
Just one sentence—

657
00:28:45,850 --> 00:28:47,380
"That was inevitable."

658
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,610
In this world,

659
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:55,720
many things are inevitable.

660
00:28:58,270 --> 00:29:01,660
What we can do is

661
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:05,770
protect what we want,

662
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:10,220
shoulder what we can bear,

663
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:15,610
and keep moving forward.

664
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:20,390
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

665
00:29:38,530 --> 00:29:39,060
Shengli!

666
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:40,620
Xu Shengli!

667
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:41,730
You're back?

668
00:29:43,090 --> 00:29:44,020
Perfect timing.

669
00:29:44,330 --> 00:29:45,250
What is this?

670
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:46,500
Didn't you ask my mom

671
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,740
about tailoring?

672
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:48,900
These are

673
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:50,700
books and magazines she collected.

674
00:29:50,700 --> 00:29:51,230
And this.

675
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:53,570
These are fabric samples.

676
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:55,640
The content is really rich.

677
00:29:55,810 --> 00:29:57,070
See if you can use them.

678
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,260
What's that reaction?

679
00:30:06,140 --> 00:30:07,460
I was thinking I should call your mom

680
00:30:07,460 --> 00:30:08,740
to thank her.

681
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:10,940
Being beautiful and kindhearted

682
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:12,420
is indeed hereditary.

683
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:13,770
You are so sweet.

684
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:17,550
Let me tell you
another piece of good news.

685
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:18,770
The singing competition

686
00:30:18,770 --> 00:30:20,050
has started its preliminaries.

687
00:30:20,050 --> 00:30:21,000
I'm about to start recording

688
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:21,750
my tape.

689
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:23,240
That's great news.

690
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:24,440
It's wonderful news.

691
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,310
Well... then...

692
00:30:25,310 --> 00:30:26,610
Is there anything I can help you with?

693
00:30:26,610 --> 00:30:29,010
No need.
Just focus on writing your script.

694
00:30:30,770 --> 00:30:32,770
It feels colder these past few days.

695
00:30:33,550 --> 00:30:35,250
Autumn in Beijing is really short.

696
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:36,530
Winter is coming soon.

697
00:30:38,330 --> 00:30:39,370
Then let's wait

698
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,860
for the next spring together.

699
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:44,120
[Seasons Change Hostel]

700
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:01,840
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

701
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:32,980
Send 5,000 back home.

702
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:38,240
Zhuang Zhuang's tuition fee.

703
00:31:54,230 --> 00:32:02,080
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

704
00:32:04,220 --> 00:32:07,610
[Guest Room]

705
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:12,050
Morning, Northeasterner.

706
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:13,080
Zhuang Zhuang.

707
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:13,940
Wait a minute.

708
00:32:20,050 --> 00:32:20,850
What's wrong?

709
00:32:26,260 --> 00:32:30,690
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

710
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,260
What happened?

711
00:32:34,010 --> 00:32:34,810
Xu

712
00:32:35,030 --> 00:32:36,700
spent most of last night alone

713
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:37,840
on the rooftop.

714
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,180
I picked them all back

715
00:32:39,180 --> 00:32:39,980
from the trash can for him.

716
00:32:39,980 --> 00:32:41,310
They should all be here.

717
00:32:44,010 --> 00:32:45,400
It's been so long.

718
00:32:46,050 --> 00:32:46,770
Xu has been struggling with

719
00:32:46,770 --> 00:32:47,940
this script every day.

720
00:32:47,750 --> 00:32:50,800
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

721
00:32:48,460 --> 00:32:49,970
But now he tore it all up.

722
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:51,460
I don't think

723
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,340
I can tell anyone else about this,

724
00:32:53,790 --> 00:32:55,720
so I had no choice but to come to you.

725
00:33:03,090 --> 00:33:04,090
Northeasterner.

726
00:33:05,570 --> 00:33:06,700
Let's just keep this

727
00:33:07,050 --> 00:33:08,250
between the two of us.

728
00:33:08,750 --> 00:33:09,880
Don't worry. I know.

729
00:33:10,420 --> 00:33:12,680
This is a basic principle of being human.

730
00:33:15,350 --> 00:33:16,810
Where are you going today?

731
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:18,840
I'm here to see you off.

732
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:21,640
Aren't you busy with the script lately?

733
00:33:21,980 --> 00:33:23,280
It's alright. Well...

734
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:24,330
Mr. He told me to come

735
00:33:24,330 --> 00:33:25,530
and experience life.

736
00:33:26,090 --> 00:33:27,000
Isn't the script

737
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,260
in its final stage now?

738
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:30,090
He said he would write the rest himself.

739
00:33:30,090 --> 00:33:31,620
He told me to come and relax.

740
00:33:37,110 --> 00:33:37,670
Alright.

741
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:39,280
My office is just ahead.

742
00:33:39,310 --> 00:33:40,880
You don't need to walk me any further.

743
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:41,210
Okay.

744
00:33:43,750 --> 00:33:44,640
So... if...

745
00:33:44,690 --> 00:33:46,940
you're not too busy
with the script lately,

746
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:48,200
could you do me a favor?

747
00:33:48,750 --> 00:33:49,410
What favor?

748
00:33:49,770 --> 00:33:51,030
I'm too busy with work.

749
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:51,960
Recording the tape

750
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,420
is too much for one person.

751
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:54,800
No problem.

752
00:33:54,830 --> 00:33:55,660
Although I don't know how to do it,

753
00:33:55,660 --> 00:33:56,590
you can teach me.

754
00:33:56,850 --> 00:33:58,180
I'll be your assistant.

755
00:33:58,380 --> 00:33:58,910
Alright.

756
00:33:59,380 --> 00:34:00,510
Thanks.

757
00:34:00,900 --> 00:34:02,480
No need to be so polite with me.

758
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:03,540
I'll be going then.

759
00:34:03,740 --> 00:34:04,270
Alright.

760
00:34:04,530 --> 00:34:05,060
Bye-bye.

761
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:21,980
Toby.

762
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:23,150
What's wrong?

763
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:24,780
Zhuang Zhuang, I was just looking for you.

764
00:34:24,780 --> 00:34:26,050
The tiger is back from abroad.

765
00:34:26,050 --> 00:34:26,800
Did you do the research

766
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:27,440
I told you to do?

767
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:28,120
I did.

768
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:29,880
I also found several references.

769
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:30,570
Are these enough?

770
00:34:30,570 --> 00:34:31,030
Okay.

771
00:34:31,300 --> 00:34:32,690
Improvise when the time comes.

772
00:34:32,690 --> 00:34:33,570
Coffee, coffee.

773
00:34:33,570 --> 00:34:35,050
Do you know the Great Wall Hotel?

774
00:34:35,050 --> 00:34:35,820
I've heard of it.

775
00:34:35,820 --> 00:34:37,020
Okay, go buy a coffee.

776
00:34:37,070 --> 00:34:37,630
Hand-ground.

777
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:38,760
No condensed milk, no sugar.

778
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:39,510
Give me the stuff.

779
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:39,909
Go now!

780
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,480
No condensed milk, no sugar.

781
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,130
The design of these sleeves

782
00:35:06,130 --> 00:35:07,070
is quite unique.

783
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,210
What were you thinking?

784
00:35:09,210 --> 00:35:09,780
Ms. Yue?

785
00:35:10,030 --> 00:35:10,840
Ms. Yue,

786
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,230
I was thinking

787
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:13,860
of making the sleeves longer

788
00:35:13,860 --> 00:35:15,090
and more flowy.

789
00:35:17,820 --> 00:35:19,110
With sleeves this heavy,

790
00:35:19,110 --> 00:35:20,630
you'd build your biceps.

791
00:35:23,690 --> 00:35:24,850
And what is this?

792
00:35:25,030 --> 00:35:25,980
Ms. Yue,

793
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:27,740
this is a magpie.

794
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:32,640
It really is a magpie.

795
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:36,110
Did you get into the art academy
through connections?

796
00:35:40,430 --> 00:35:41,070
Tracy,

797
00:35:41,690 --> 00:35:42,750
where are you from?

798
00:35:43,590 --> 00:35:44,900
I think you can

799
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:46,320
wear this dress at your wedding

800
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:47,250
in your village.

801
00:35:48,210 --> 00:35:48,840
Not bad.

802
00:35:50,050 --> 00:35:51,150
Your Group 1

803
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:52,280
has very good taste.

804
00:35:52,420 --> 00:35:53,000
These are the clothes

805
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:53,980
you spent a month

806
00:35:54,010 --> 00:35:55,280
designing,

807
00:35:55,300 --> 00:35:55,710
right?

808
00:35:56,550 --> 00:35:57,750
I'm sorry, Ms. Yue...

809
00:35:59,260 --> 00:36:00,060
Little mouth—

810
00:36:04,170 --> 00:36:04,820
Lucy.

811
00:36:04,980 --> 00:36:06,040
She's calling you.

812
00:36:06,860 --> 00:36:07,190
Me?

813
00:36:07,230 --> 00:36:07,980
Lucy.

814
00:36:08,340 --> 00:36:08,900
Coffee.

815
00:36:10,050 --> 00:36:10,750
Ms. Yue,

816
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:12,010
here's your coffee.

817
00:36:12,380 --> 00:36:13,650
I was afraid it would get cold,

818
00:36:13,650 --> 00:36:15,380
so I bought a thermos on the way.

819
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:18,940
Ms. Yue.

820
00:36:20,630 --> 00:36:21,300
Ms. Yue, well...

821
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:23,050
our Group 2
has also found some references.

822
00:36:23,050 --> 00:36:25,250
Zhuang Zhuang, please introduce them.

823
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:26,210
Ms. Yue...

824
00:36:26,210 --> 00:36:27,050
Skip Group 2.

825
00:36:27,860 --> 00:36:29,280
Raise your lifestyle aesthetics

826
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,440
to the company's entry-level standard,

827
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,570
and then we'll talk.

828
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:41,980
Was I blind?

829
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:43,980
Was I blind

830
00:36:44,070 --> 00:36:45,320
to hire you, a bunch of losers,

831
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,000
into the company,

832
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:46,880
just to have you design

833
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:47,780
this kind of trash for me?

834
00:36:47,780 --> 00:36:49,000
Jonathan is coming

835
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,030
to see the samples in a few days.

836
00:36:50,030 --> 00:36:51,360
See the samples. Got it?

837
00:36:55,550 --> 00:36:57,480
Figure out a solution yourselves.

838
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,160
You'll get used to it.

839
00:37:15,810 --> 00:37:16,440
Toby.

840
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:27,960
Just now... Sit down.

841
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:30,180
Sorry about just now.

842
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:31,550
If I hadn't dealt with it

843
00:37:31,550 --> 00:37:32,250
in time,

844
00:37:32,510 --> 00:37:34,340
she would have scolded everyone again.

845
00:37:34,340 --> 00:37:35,670
Keep this for yourself.

846
00:37:36,150 --> 00:37:36,750
Thank you.

847
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:39,280
I should be sorry.

848
00:37:39,510 --> 00:37:40,480
I should have

849
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:41,840
prepared the coffee earlier

850
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:43,300
and put it in Ms. Yue's cup.

851
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:44,950
I'll know better next time.

852
00:37:45,780 --> 00:37:47,240
You've got a good mindset.

853
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:49,370
You didn't get discouraged at all.

854
00:37:49,550 --> 00:37:51,340
That's just how she talks.

855
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:53,130
But if you stay here long enough,

856
00:37:53,130 --> 00:37:54,530
you'll definitely grow.

857
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:56,130
When I first came here,

858
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:57,930
I cried every day when I got home.

859
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:00,460
Oh, right.

860
00:38:01,820 --> 00:38:02,420
Lucy...

861
00:38:02,730 --> 00:38:03,570
Who is Lucy?

862
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,560
Did Ms. Yue mistake me for someone else?

863
00:38:06,690 --> 00:38:08,420
I forgot to tell you about that.

864
00:38:10,090 --> 00:38:10,710
Here,

865
00:38:10,780 --> 00:38:12,580
as long as you're her assistant,

866
00:38:12,730 --> 00:38:13,860
you're called Lucy.

867
00:38:14,210 --> 00:38:16,300
The head of Group 1 is called Tracy.

868
00:38:16,730 --> 00:38:18,590
The head of Group 2 is called Toby.

869
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,820
She thinks it's easier to remember.

870
00:38:20,820 --> 00:38:22,350
Just treat it as a job title.

871
00:38:23,190 --> 00:38:23,720
Alright.

872
00:38:25,780 --> 00:38:27,280
So... is there anything else

873
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:28,280
I can do right now?

874
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:29,530
Looks like we're on a very tight deadline

875
00:38:29,530 --> 00:38:30,500
for our design drafts.

876
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:31,650
But I don't know

877
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:33,530
whether I should submit them now.

878
00:38:35,670 --> 00:38:37,090
Our boss

879
00:38:37,170 --> 00:38:38,170
is just like this.

880
00:38:38,690 --> 00:38:40,210
She said she wouldn't look at them today,

881
00:38:40,210 --> 00:38:42,090
but tomorrow she might want to see them.

882
00:38:42,090 --> 00:38:43,530
She may say she doesn't like you today,

883
00:38:43,530 --> 00:38:45,670
but she could really like you tomorrow.

884
00:38:45,670 --> 00:38:47,400
She's totally unpredictable.

885
00:38:48,510 --> 00:38:50,660
Anyway, just keep them ready.

886
00:38:50,730 --> 00:38:51,360
If there's anything you don't understand,

887
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,020
just ask me.

888
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:53,880
If you really don't dare to submit them,

889
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:54,800
I'll do it for you.

890
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:55,150
Okay.

891
00:38:56,460 --> 00:38:57,320
Oh right, Toby.

892
00:38:59,150 --> 00:39:00,410
What is your real name?

893
00:39:01,980 --> 00:39:04,910
You should use your real name
outside of work, right?

894
00:39:05,300 --> 00:39:05,860
Well...

895
00:39:12,150 --> 00:39:13,280
My name is Li Daqing.

896
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:16,630
Dad,

897
00:39:16,860 --> 00:39:17,620
I'm back.

898
00:39:19,150 --> 00:39:19,880
Liangliang.

899
00:39:20,630 --> 00:39:21,560
Where is Ranran?

900
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,600
She can't come over all the time.

901
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:26,240
Red bean buns.

902
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,210
Your mom made them.

903
00:39:27,210 --> 00:39:28,340
Take them to Ranran.

904
00:39:28,510 --> 00:39:29,340
Why aren't you two

905
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:30,840
this nice to me?

906
00:39:32,820 --> 00:39:33,610
You are not allowed to play

907
00:39:33,610 --> 00:39:35,130
those noisy tunes later. You hear me?

908
00:39:35,130 --> 00:39:35,840
Okay.

909
00:39:36,510 --> 00:39:37,530
I'll play a gentle one for you.

910
00:39:37,530 --> 00:39:37,930
You...

911
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:46,690
Do you think we can get the money back?

912
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:57,280
Who allowed you to play here?

913
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,090
Stop playing!

914
00:39:58,360 --> 00:39:58,820
Your spit

915
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:00,080
splashed into my bowl!

916
00:40:01,070 --> 00:40:01,670
I'm sorry.

917
00:40:01,730 --> 00:40:03,590
I'll get you a fresh plate of this.

918
00:40:04,090 --> 00:40:05,340
You think one plate of food
is enough to brush us off,

919
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:05,880
right?

920
00:40:08,030 --> 00:40:09,400
What the hell were you playing?

921
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,010
Let me see.

922
00:40:10,610 --> 00:40:11,470
Don't touch it.

923
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:12,340
Why are you touching it?

924
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:13,220
What's with the attitude?

925
00:40:13,220 --> 00:40:14,320
I'll smash it!

926
00:40:14,340 --> 00:40:16,260
Don't touch my stuff!

927
00:40:16,860 --> 00:40:17,400
How dare you hit him?

928
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:18,610
You lousy busker!

929
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:20,010
Trying to pick a fight with us?

930
00:40:20,010 --> 00:40:20,690
Wait a minute.

931
00:40:20,690 --> 00:40:22,290
Let me take off my saxophone.

932
00:40:22,460 --> 00:40:23,050
Screw you!

933
00:40:23,050 --> 00:40:23,650
Screw you!

934
00:40:27,380 --> 00:40:28,640
Still wanna act tough?

935
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,550
You little brat!

936
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,210
Take that!

937
00:40:49,670 --> 00:40:50,400
What is this?

938
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,130
What is this?

939
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:54,170
An instrument.

940
00:40:54,170 --> 00:40:55,170
What instrument?

941
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:56,820
A... A saxophone.

942
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,150
A saxophone!

943
00:40:58,260 --> 00:40:59,170
It's not a piece of junk

944
00:40:59,170 --> 00:40:59,970
like you said!

945
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:01,470
Also!

946
00:41:01,860 --> 00:41:02,720
What does he do?

947
00:41:04,110 --> 00:41:06,970
He is a saxophone artist!

948
00:41:07,170 --> 00:41:08,380
He's not a lousy busker

949
00:41:08,380 --> 00:41:09,370
like you said!

950
00:41:11,420 --> 00:41:11,960
Get out!

951
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:14,270
You don't deserve to listen!

952
00:41:14,500 --> 00:41:15,210
Get lost!

953
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:21,010
Get out!

954
00:41:44,590 --> 00:41:45,050
Dad.

955
00:41:59,900 --> 00:42:03,590
[Beijing Cuisine]

956
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:03,360
Thank you, Dad.

957
00:42:08,440 --> 00:42:09,380
Is that how a son

958
00:42:09,420 --> 00:42:10,610
talks to his father?

959
00:42:15,030 --> 00:42:17,290
It was my first time seeing you like this.

960
00:42:17,460 --> 00:42:18,510
I've never seen it before.

961
00:42:18,510 --> 00:42:19,530
You brat.

962
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:21,180
Remember this.

963
00:42:23,090 --> 00:42:24,690
I, Tao Baohua, am the only one

964
00:42:25,230 --> 00:42:26,590
allowed to hit my son.

965
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:28,540
Nobody else

966
00:42:29,650 --> 00:42:31,130
can lay a finger on you.

967
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:43,900
Should I come back tomorrow?

968
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:45,070
Of course.

969
00:42:46,260 --> 00:42:47,480
Why shouldn't you?

970
00:42:47,740 --> 00:42:57,280
[Opening Time: 5:30 a.m.]

971
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:50,810
If I come back a few more times,

972
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,650
our family business

973
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,510
will be ruined by me.
